HEADWORD: Equidistant
<hw>E`qui*dis"tant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aequidistans</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>; <ets>aequus</ets> equal +
<ets>distans</ets> distant: cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧quidistant</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Being at an equal distance from the same point or thing.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>E`qui*dis"tant*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>
<rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
